Chilean Stocks: Cencosud, CTI and Molibdenos & Metales

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-18T16:11:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/chilean-stocks-cencosud-cti-and-molibdenos-metales.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:46 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 2.2 percent to 4,136.64.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) retreated 1.5 percent to 2,921
pesos, the biggest decline in a week.  Latin America ’s third-
largest retailer by sales dropped as global stock markets
retreated amid concern growth is slowing in the U.S. and
European banks lack sufficient capital.  CTI Cia Tecno Industrial SA (CTI)  , a Chilean home
appliances producer, jumped 7.9 percent to 34 pesos and earlier
rose 24 percent to a record 39 pesos. CTI’s controller, Chilean
holding company  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK) , confirmed it is in
negotiations to sell the company.  Molibdenos & Metales SA (MOLYMET CC) fell 2.5 percent to
7,800 pesos and earlier slumped 11 percent, its biggest intraday
drop since November. The Chilean molybdenum processor reported
yesterday a 21 percent decline in second-quarter net income.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
